overview:
`Functions` perform a specific task given an input and an output.

```
struct ExampleView: View {
    var body: some View {
        Text(getFruit())
   }

    func getFruit() -> String {
        return ["🍌🍌", "🍏🍏", "🍑🍑"].randomElement()!
    }
}
```
Apple has a great overview on Swift `Functions` [here](https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/LanguageGuide/Functions.html).
